<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7274> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7274" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. mil. of uncertain date, but probably before 200. An early inscription of Tusculum reads as follows: M. Fourio C. f. tribunos / militare de praidad Maurte dedet (CIL 1(2).2.49-ILS 3142- ILLRP 221; cf. CIL 1(2).2.48). Munzer suggests that his cognomen was Crassipes (see no. 56) and that he was a praetor in 187 and 173 (MRR 1.368, 408). See Suolahti, Junior Officers 309, 405. (RS, CP; LRT) Refer also to ILLRP 100; and to P. Pocetti, MEFR 94, 1982, 657-674.\n" .
